2014-02-26 22:40:14	--	- CARD, ORSON SCOTT [1951-].  Born in Richland, Washington, Card grew up in
2014-02-26 22:40:14	--	- California, Arizona, and Utah.  He lived in Brazil for two years as an
2014-02-26 22:40:14	--	- unpaid missionary for the Mormon Church.  Author of the Ender and Alvin
2014-02-26 22:40:14	--	- Maker books, Card's science fiction and fantasy work is strongly influenced
2014-02-26 22:40:14	--	- by his Mormon cultural background.  The first author to win the Hugo and
2014-02-26 22:40:14	--	- Nebula novel awards two years in a row, Card currently lives in Greensboro,
2014-02-26 22:40:14	--	- North Carolina, US.
